	<text xml:lang="en">
		<body>
<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><p>By applying to our U-M4,5 spectra the following sum rules developed by Thole et al. and by Carra et al.</p><p>we obtain an orbital moment of &lt;Lz&gt; = -1.66 µB and an effective spin moment &lt;Sz&gt; + 3&lt;Tz&gt; = 1.05 µB , where &lt;Tz&gt; is the magnetic dipole moment. We have considered nh=12 according to a 5f 2 configuration.</p><p>A comparison of the experimental value of the orbital moment and with that obtained by LSDA+U calculations suggests the need to consider a large value of the Coulomb repulsion for the UBeGe in order to reproduce the experimental values.</p></div><figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="fig_0"><head>Fig. 1 .</head><label>1</label><figDesc>Fig. 1. U-M5 and M4 XAS (red) and XMCD (blue) spectra of UBeGe measured at T =2 K under an applied field of H = 3.0 T at the ID12 beamline of ESRF using circular polarized soft X-rays.</figDesc><graphic coords="2,33.95,51.00,324.60,235.80" type="bitmap" /></figure>
<figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="fig_1"><head>Fig. 2 .</head><label>2</label><figDesc>Fig. 2. Hysteresis of the XMCD signal of the U M4 edge measured at 2 K.</figDesc><graphic coords="2,33.95,329.30,208.45,148.40" type="bitmap" /></figure>
		</body>
